subSubSection.paragraph:
Primary thallus
subpersistent, laciniate squamules, esorediate, epruinose; 
podetia
common, grayish green, sometimes brown with age, 0.8–2.5 (–3) cm tall, always scyphose and shaped like a cone; cups, when well developed, abundantly and repeatedly proliferating (forming 1-2 tiers); 
surface
slightly corticate at the base, otherwise decorticated, basally typically ±finely squamulose, becoming microsquamulose, densely granulose or farinose sorediate; 
pycnidia
with hyaline jelly; 
apothecia
with brown jelly.
